data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":410,"item_id":"msg_007d4a0bb4f155eb00693b377cb56c8195b18c086360c4c57b","output_index":4,"content_index":0,"text":"I’m not sure which context you mean — “secondary agent” can mean different things in different systems. Which of these fits your situation, or tell me more about the system?\n\n- A multi-agent AI system or chatbot\n- A backup/failover process in distributed systems\n- A secondary (adjunct) agent in robotics or control systems\n- A chemical/biological secondary agent (e.g., adjuvant)\n- A support microservice / worker / background job\n- Something else (please describe)\n\nWhile you decide, here are common capabilities a “secondary agent” often has, with short examples:\n\n- Redundancy / failover: stands ready to take over if the primary fails (e.g., standby server).\n- Monitoring and health checks: continuously observes system status and alerts or triggers remediation.\n- Delegated task handling: performs auxiliary or long-running tasks the primary delegates (e.g., background processing, batch jobs).\n- Data aggregation and preprocessing: collects, cleans, and summarizes data for the primary agent.\n- Security and validation: enforces policies, validates inputs, filters malicious content.\n- Proxying and mediation: acts as a gateway or translator between systems (protocol translation, API orchestration).\n- Specialized processing: handles tasks requiring different models/resources (e.g., vision agent in a multimodal system).\n- Rate-limiting and throttling: controls or queues requests to protect the primary.\n- Logging, auditing, and observability: records actions and provides traces for debugging and compliance.\n- Escalation / routing: decides when to escalate to the primary or to humans, and routes tasks accordingly.\n- Testing and sandboxing: runs risky operations in isolation before committing results to the main system.\n- User interaction fallback: handles follow-ups, clarifying questions, or less critical interactions.\n\nIf you tell me the exact domain (AI agents, servers, robots, chemicals, etc.), I’ll list the most relevant abilities and give concrete examples or implementation patterns.","logprobs":[]}

